Pan Africa Insurance Falls to 16-Month Low as Profit Drops

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-08-11T12:36:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/pan-africa-insurance-slumps-to-16-month-low-as-profit-declines.html
Pan Africa Insurance Holdings Ltd. (PAIL) ,
the Kenyan unit of South Africaâ€™s  Sanlam Ltd. (SLM) , slumped to a 16-
month low after saying profit fell 65 percent in the six months
through June.  The stock fell 5.2 percent to 27.50 shillings by the 3 p.m.
close in the capital, Nairobi, the lowest level since April
2010.  Net income tumbled to 73 million shillings ($776,000) from
210.6 million shilling a year earlier, Pan Africa Insurance said
in an e-mailed statement to the stock exchange yesterday.  Pan Africa dropped 23 percent in July, making it the worst-
performing stock on the Kenyan exchange last month, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
